    "spell_type": "spell",
    "subtype": "spell",
    "text": "You let out the mighty cry of a majestic eagle that pierces eardrums. This cry deals 4d8 sonic damage. Each creature in the area must attempt a Fortitude saving throw.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 16,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Auditory",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 453,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 32,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "e32d877417a40fe977d27634dc14f99f",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Concentrate",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 454,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "An action with this trait requires a degree of mental concentration and discipline.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 104,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "6a0bf3cdfe7c0fc427c7b8ea9310f113",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Manipulate",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "You must physically manipulate an item or make gestures to use an action with this trait. Creatures without a suitable appendage can\u2019t perform actions with this trait. Manipulate actions often trigger reactions.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 147,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "062d349c50c70477d316b8620025454e",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Sonic",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 461",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 461",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 461,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "An effect with the sonic trait functions only if it makes sound, meaning it has no effect in an area of silence or in a vacuum. This is different from an auditory spell, which is effective only if the target can hear it. A sonic effect might deal sonic damage.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
    "type": "stat_block_section"
  },
  "type": "spell"
